8 PROPOSED COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to special education; defining term;
requiring certain qualifications for special
10 education administrators; requiring State Board of
Education to issue certain acknowledgement of
11 competency; requiring training cover certain topics;
requiring competency exam; exempting certain special
12 education administrators from requirement; providing
for codification; providing an effective date; and
13 declaring an emergency.
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-189.3 of Title 70, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. For this section, "special education administrator" means
20 the director and assistant director of a special education program
21 for a school district.
22 B. Beginning July 1, 2025, no school district shall employ a
23 special education administrator unless the individual:
24
Req. No. 12812 Page 1
1 1. Holds a valid standard teaching certificate issued by the
2 State Board of Education; and
3 2. Except as provided for in subsection D of this section,
4 obtains an acknowledgment of competency within one (1) year of being
5 employed as a special education administrator.
6 C. The State Board of Education shall issue an acknowledgement
7 of competency in the area of mild-moderate disabilities, severe-
8 profound disabilities, or comprehensive special education to a
9 special education administrator who has:
10 1. Satisfactorily completed a one-hundred-fifty-clock-hour
11 special education program prescribed by the State Board of Education
12 which shall include training on the rules and regulations for the
13 Individuals with Disabilities Act (IDEA); and
14 2. Achieved at least a seventy percent (70%) on a competency
15 examination in the area of mild-moderate disabilities, severe-
16 profound disabilities, or comprehensive special education
17 administered by the State Department of Education.
18 D. An individual who has a valid Special Education Teaching
19 Certificate as provided for in Sections 6-122.7, 6-122.8, or 6-122.9
20 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall not be required to obtain
21 an acknowledgement of competency.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
Req. No. 12812 Page 2
1 decl ared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
2 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
